hopobject.body: How much will it cost to send this letter to ? periactin yahoo Scott Walker, the conservative governor of Wisconsin, triumphed over an effort to recall him, exposing the process as the massive waste of time that it often is. Walker was democratically elected in a free and fair contest and then proceeded to mount an anti-union agenda that horrified his opponents. Fair enough. If the state's residents didn't like it, they could lobby their state legislators to overrule the governor, or start mounting a campaign to defeat him in the next election. Instead, they began a recall effort – winning by getting enough signatures to have a recall election, then losing by failing to recall him. Polls at the time showed that some residents simply didn't like the idea of a recall – and they have a strong point.
